title: Mirza-Hingis ease into Wuhan Open women's doubles semis
text: Mirza-Hingis ease into Wuhan Open women's doubles semis Friday, 9 October 2015 (1 minute ago) *Wuhan, Oct.1 (ANI): Indian tennis ace Sania Mirza continued her rampaging form, alongside Swiss partner Martina Hingis by storming into the semi-finals of the Wuhan Open women's doubles event on Thursday.* Wuhan, Oct.1 (ANI): Indian tennis ace Sania Mirza continued her rampaging form, alongside Swiss partner Martina Hingis by storming into the semi-finals of the Wuhan Open women's doubles event on Thursday. The Indo-Swiss duo claimed a 6-2, 6-2 win over the fifth-seeded American pair of Raquel Kops-Jones and Abigail Spears in the quarterfinal clash that lasted 58 minutes. Mirza and Hingis clinched their sixth women's doubles title of the year by winning the Guangzhou Open last month. They have also won two Grand Slam titles at Wimbledon and the US Open, since joining forces in March. (ANI)
